Verification:
  1. Printable ASCII/UTF-8 characters pass through as bytes
  2. Special keys: Enter→\r, Backspace→0x7F, Tab→\t, Escape→\x1b
  3. Arrow keys map to CSI sequences (\x1b[A/B/C/D)
  4. Ctrl+A..Z produce control bytes 0x01..0x1A
  5. F1-F4 use SS3 format, F5-F12 use CSI ~ format
  6. Navigation keys: Home/End/Insert/Delete/PageUp/PageDown all mapped
  7. Key releases and modifier-only presses correctly return None
  8. 39 new tests covering all key translation paths
